cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with surgical motion and the development of an architecture to model the conditional distribution over future motion given past motion. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as the paper involves learning meaningful representations of surgical motion. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category as the paper involves the development of an architecture that combines an RNN encoder-decoder and mixture density networks (MDNs) to model the conditional distribution over future motion given past motion. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possible category as the paper involves the use of unsupervised learning to learn meaningful representations of surgical motion. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper involves information retrieval and searching a database of surgical motion using a motion-based query.
